🔐 Data Encryption & Protection

FDE (Full Disk Encryption)

Encrypts the entire storage drive

Protects data when a device is powered off or stolen

Prevents unauthorized access to stored data

Key Escrow

Secure storage of encryption keys with a trusted third party

Allows authorized entities to recover keys when necessary

Ensures controlled access while maintaining security

🚨 Intrusion Detection & Prevention

NIPS (Network Intrusion Prevention System)

Monitors network traffic in real time

Detects and blocks malicious activity

Can automatically stop threats rather than just alerting like IDS

🔋 Resilience & Infrastructure

UPS (Uninterruptible Power Supply)

Provides short-term backup power

Maintains system availability during power outages

Allows safe shutdown or continued operation temporarily

🏢 Physical Security Controls

Cameras and Warning Signs

Serve as both:

Deterrent controls

Detective controls

Discourage malicious behavior and record activity

📦 Integrity Verification

File Hashing

Used to verify that downloaded files have not been altered

Hash values from the vendor are compared to downloaded files

Ensures file integrity and authenticity

🖥 Virtualization

Allows multiple virtual machines (VMs) to run on a single physical server

Benefits:

Hardware efficiency

Isolation between environments

Reduced need for multiple physical servers

